plore the impact which forced migration and prolonged conflict have had, and continue to have, on the lives of these refugee youth and their families. This study examines refugee communities closely linked with the United Nations High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) and a host of other UN agencies in the case of the Sahrawi and near total lack of humanitarian aid in the case of Afghan refugees in Iran.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aRefugee childrenxRelocationzAfghanistan. 0aRefugee childrenzMiddle EastxSocial conditions. 0aSahrawi (African people)xRelocation. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aChatty, Dawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChatty, Dawn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCozza, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrivello, Gina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiddian-Qasmiyeh, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoodfar, Homa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamal, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonsutti, Alessandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184545818840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845458188423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781845458188/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aP